The paper proposes a low-complexity message passing algorithm for sparse vector recovery, which involves processing Bernoulli and Gaussian messages jointly. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a lower bound for the mean square error (MSE) of the algorithm, which could also place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with convergence speed, which could place it in the Mathematical Methods (cs.MM) sub-category.
